Psalm 87-3 <t><f>ⓔ</f> Glorious things of you are spoken, </t><t>O <f>ⓕ</f>city of God. <pb/><i>Selah</i> <pb/></t>
Psalm 87-4 <pb/><t>Among those who <f>ⓖ</f>know me I mention <f>ⓗ</f>Rahab and Babylon; </t><t>behold, Philistia and Tyre, with <f>ⓘ</f>Cush <f>[1]</f> — </t><t>“This one was born there,” they say.</t>
Psalm 87-5 <t>And of Zion it shall be said, </t><t>“This one and that one were born in her”; </t><t>for the Most High himself will <f>ⓙ</f>establish her.</t>
Psalm 87-6 <t>The LORD records as he <f>ⓚ</f>registers the peoples, </t><t>“This one was born there.” <pb/><i>Selah</i> <pb/></t>
Psalm 87-7 <pb/><t><f>ⓛ</f> Singers and <f>ⓜ</f>dancers alike say, </t><t>“All my <f>ⓝ</f>springs are in you.” </t>